# ============================================
# 7-Project Supabase Configuration Example
# ============================================
# Copy this file to config.properties and add your credentials
# config.properties is gitignored and will not be committed

# ============================================
# QUICK SETUP: SINGLE PROJECT (500MB)
# ============================================
# Perfect for personal use - just fill in one project!

# Your Supabase project URL
supabase.auth.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.reading.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.library.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.book_reviews.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.chapter_reviews.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.badges.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.analytics.url=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Your Supabase anon/public key (NOT the service_role key!)
# Get this from: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/YOUR_PROJECT/settings/api
supabase.auth.key=your-anon-key-here
supabase.reading.key=your-anon-key-here
supabase.library.key=your-anon-key-here
supabase.book_reviews.key=your-anon-key-here
supabase.chapter_reviews.key=your-anon-key-here
supabase.badges.key=your-anon-key-here
supabase.analytics.key=your-anon-key-here

# ============================================
# ADVANCED: MULTI-PROJECT SETUP (3.5GB)
# ============================================
# For maximum storage, create 7 separate projects
# and replace the URLs and keys above with different values

# Example multi-project configuration:
# supabase.auth.url=https://auth-abc123.supabase.co
# supabase.auth.key=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.auth-key
# 
# supabase.reading.url=https://reading-def456.supabase.co
# supabase.reading.key=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.reading-key
# 
# supabase.library.url=https://library-ghi789.supabase.co
# supabase.library.key=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.library-key
# 
# ... and so on for all 7 projects


# ============================================
# NOTES
# ============================================
# 1. For single project: Use same URL/key for all 7 entries
# 2. For multi-project: Use different URL/key for each entry
# 3. Never commit config.properties to git
# 4. Use anon/public keys only (visible in browser)
# 5. Deploy appropriate SQL schemas to your project(s)
# 6. See QUICK_START_7PROJECT.md for detailed guide

# ============================================
# WHAT EACH PROJECT STORES
# ============================================
# Auth:            User accounts and authentication
# Reading:         Reading progress and bookmarks
# Library:         Synced books and chapters
# Book Reviews:    Book ratings and reviews
# Chapter Reviews: Chapter ratings and reviews
# Badges:          Achievement badges and NFT wallets
# Analytics:       Leaderboard and statistics

# ============================================
# GETTING YOUR CREDENTIALS
# ============================================
# 1. Go to https://app.supabase.com
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Settings → API
# 4. Copy "Project URL" → use as supabase.*.url
# 5. Copy "anon public" key → use as supabase.*.key
# 6. Repeat for each project if using multi-project setup
